Technically, Dang is proficient in programming languages such as Python and SQL, with hands-on experience in libraries like Numpy and Pandas for data manipulation and analysis. Their understanding of data structures, including trees, graphs, queues, and stacks, provides a solid foundation for more complex AI architectures. While their current experience does not include direct work with databases, devops, or cloud platforms, their academic background and project management certification indicate potential for quick adaptation to these technologies. With a strong educational foundation and certifications in German language proficiency, project management, and English proficiency (IELTS Academic – Band 6.5), Dang Nguyen Le is well-positioned to leverage their technical skills and knowledge in machine learning, deep learning, and data analysis to contribute to AI engineering projects, particularly those involving CNN, RNN, and Transformers, and to grow into more senior roles as they accumulate commercial experience.